1
00:00:02,980 --> 00:00:06,980
That time has come once more.

2
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:09,480
Have the students been informed?

3
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:11,030
They will all be notified by day's end.

4
00:00:12,530 --> 00:00:15,780
At the academy, some will rise and some will fall.

5
00:00:16,490 --> 00:00:18,700
This is where their paths begin to diverge.

6
00:01:54,010 --> 00:01:55,720
Training camp?

7
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,550
It's that time of year again, huh?

8
00:01:57,550 --> 00:01:58,510
What's this about?

9
00:01:59,050 --> 00:02:01,970
You had something like this in middle school, didn't you?

10
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:04,470
We're going to a camp and staying there for a few nights.

11
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:09,020
Really? I had no idea the academy did stuff like that.

12
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:11,440
Why are you trembling, Tadokoro?

13
00:02:11,690 --> 00:02:17,650
This camp represents the first circle of hell
 for new high school students.

14
00:02:18,570 --> 00:02:22,010
All first-years will be tasked with
 grueling cooking projects every day,

15
00:02:22,010 --> 00:02:24,540
in a remote location in the mountains.

16
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,750
If we don't earn a passing score,

17
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,460
we face immediate expulsion.

18
00:02:29,170 --> 00:02:31,750
They claim it's an opportunity to strengthen our bonds,

19
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:38,050
it's a merciless gauntlet for
 weeding out the weak!

20
00:02:40,390 --> 00:02:42,800
This is what they mean by
 education through competition.

21
00:02:43,850 --> 00:02:45,810
The director spoke of the one percent.

22
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:48,810
This is where the selection process really begins.

23
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:53,940
Isshiki-senpai, you went to
 this camp last year, right?

24
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:55,730
Yes, of course.

25
00:02:55,730 --> 00:03:01,450
When I attended last year's training camp,
dozens were expelled and sent home each day.

26
00:03:01,450 --> 00:03:02,910
Expelled?

27
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:05,490
After one camp some years ago,

28
00:03:05,490 --> 00:03:08,450
half of the participating students
 were shown the door.

29
00:03:08,450 --> 00:03:10,500
Half?

30
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,250
Megumi?!

31
00:03:11,670 --> 00:03:14,670
I'm grateful for the time
 we've had together, everyone.

32
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:17,630
Megumi!

33
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:21,680
Okay, so we can bring playing cards and shogi sets,

34
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:24,030
but video games aren't allowed.

35
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:26,560
What, they don't give us any time for taking baths?

36
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,810
Hey, Yukihira!

37
00:03:28,270 --> 00:03:31,020
How can you be so carefree and be planning your trip already?

38
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:33,520
Megumi's practically on her deathbed here!

39
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:35,690
Half the class will make it, right?

40
00:03:35,690 --> 00:03:37,690
All we have to do is be in that half.

41
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:41,490
I'm also quite certain

42
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:45,370
that everyone in Polar Star
 will come back smiling.

43
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,850
I'll make it back here!

44
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:51,770
I sure will!

45
00:03:51,770 --> 00:03:53,000
Of course.

46
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:54,630
You're right.

47
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:57,000
We're all so determined!

48
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,920
We Polar Stars strike fear into the hearts of men!

49
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:01,010
We do?

50
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:04,160
Let's dominate this camp!

51
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,400
That's the spirit.

52
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,850
Fumio-san and I will hold the fort.

53
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,810
Give it your best shot!

54
00:04:10,810 --> 00:04:11,890
Yeah!

55
00:04:10,810 --> 00:04:11,890
Okay!

56
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,690
Got it!

57
00:04:11,890 --> 00:04:13,440
I'm on fire!

58
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,100
That concludes the overview.

59
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:17,480
Please don't forget anything.

60
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:19,530
You'll depart in three days.

61
00:04:19,530 --> 00:04:21,570
Everyone is to assemble at 6:00 AM.

62
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:22,490
I see.

63
00:04:22,490 --> 00:04:24,320
Thank you, Hisako.

64
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:48,930
My stomach hurts!

65
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:51,270
I'm kind of getting jaded.

66
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,810
A'ight!

67
00:04:52,810 --> 00:04:54,140
Let's go!

68
00:04:54,140 --> 00:04:56,730
Off to the friendship and
 team-building camp from hell!

69
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:58,980
Nothing's gonna surprise me any more!

70
00:05:20,210 --> 00:05:22,130
Wow!

71
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:24,220
Th-This is our "camp" site?

72
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:26,380
Guess this school is full of rich guys for a reason.

73
00:05:26,380 --> 00:05:29,050
They even run a big-ass hotel.

74
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:33,270
All of the hotels and inns around
 here belong to Tohtsuki.

75
00:05:33,580 --> 00:05:35,730
Heh, doesn't surprise me one bit!

76
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:40,060
They manage a dozen or so accommodations under the Tohtsuki Resorts brand,

77
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:44,940
and graduates often end up working in the resorts' culinary division.

78
00:05:44,940 --> 00:05:48,320
I've heard it costs upwards of 80,000 yen
 per night at these places.

79
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:50,700
That's like a month's rent!

80
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:53,490
I'm definitely not surprised at all!

81
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,910
You're totally surprised, Souma-kun.

82
00:05:55,910 --> 00:05:59,200
Wait, so we're staying here tonight?

83
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,370
Wow, this is super exciting!

84
00:06:01,370 --> 00:06:03,420
<i>If</i> we can survive today's task.

85
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:04,510
Boo!

86
00:06:04,510 --> 00:06:07,220
Ibusaki, you're such a downer.

87
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,510
I'm just being realistic.

88
00:06:09,050 --> 00:06:09,720
See?

89
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:12,100
There's an assembly as soon as we drop off our bags.

90
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,500
Okay.

91
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,110
<i>It's too quiet.</i>

92
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:27,530
<i>It's hard to believe that nearly
 a thousand students are here.</i>

93
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:28,860
<i>That's right.</i>

94
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:32,200
<i>What's about to start is the training camp from hell.</i>

95
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:35,880
<i>How many of us will survive?</i>

96
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:40,790
Look, it's Nikumi!

97
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:42,380
Y-Yukihira!

98
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:45,250
Been a while, Nikumi!

99
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:47,210
You're not nervous at all, huh?

100
00:06:47,210 --> 00:06:48,550
Hey, Yukihira-kun!

101
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:50,010
Why are you calling her by a nickname?

102
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:52,050
Huh? But she's fine with it.

103
00:06:52,050 --> 00:06:53,050
Right, Nikumi?

104
00:06:53,050 --> 00:06:54,720
Of course not!

105
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:54,720
See?

106
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,930
It's the transfer student.

107
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,930
She likes it.

108
00:06:55,930 --> 00:06:57,390
Yukihira Souma.

109
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,310
Be careful, Yukihira.

110
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:04,230
Huh? About what?

111
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:06,070
Good morning, students!

112
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:10,660
I will now provide an overview of this camp.

113
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:13,200
You're scheduled to stay here
 for five nights and six days.

114
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:16,240
During this time, you'll split off into several groups

115
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:20,210
and take on a new assignment each day.

116
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:24,920
Students whose instructors' evaluations fall below a certain baseline will be failed,

117
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,880
sent back to the academy,

118
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,090
and expelled.

119
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:32,680
To evaluate your tasks,

120
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,510
we have invited some guest lecturers.

121
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:35,850
Guests?

122
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:39,770
They're Tohtsuki alumni who have graciously agreed to join us,

123
00:07:39,770 --> 00:07:41,770
in spite of their busy schedules.

124
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:47,980
Tohtsuki alumni?

125
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:49,490
That means...

126
00:07:49,490 --> 00:07:53,950
they're all geniuses who managed to remain in the 90th percentile!

127
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:03,120
Hm, you over there.

128
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:04,750
Nine rows back,

129
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:07,840
the boy with a scar on his eyebrow.

130
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:09,920
Oh, sorry.

131
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,170
I mean the one to your right.

132
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,900
Yeah, you.

133
00:08:13,590 --> 00:08:14,720
You're expelled.

134
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:15,470
You may leave now.

135
00:08:15,470 --> 00:08:16,180
What?!

136
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:19,390
Your hair product has a citrus scent.

137
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:22,640
It interferes with the aroma of the food.

138
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:25,180
We <i>do</i> need to pay attention
 to our sense of style.

139
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:28,650
If chefs have no sense of style,
 their dishes will have no appeal.

140
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:32,570
But you should choose an unscented hair product from now on.

141
00:08:32,570 --> 00:08:33,700
Wait!

142
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:36,320
I'm getting expelled just for <i>that</i>?!

143
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:39,740
Just <i>that</i> can be enough to lose your customers.

144
00:08:41,010 --> 00:08:44,420
Are you trying to destroy my restaurant?

145
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:49,180
Farewell, student.

146
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:52,590
Who's that?

147
00:08:52,590 --> 00:08:54,550
It's Chef Shinomiya!

148
00:08:54,550 --> 00:08:58,510
He's the first Japanese national to win the French Pluspol award!

149
00:08:58,510 --> 00:08:59,180
Not to mention...

150
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,640
Onstage are also Chef Mizuhara from F,

151
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:07,100
and Head Chef Sekimori from the sushi restaurant Ginza Hinowa!

152
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:08,520
Wow!

153
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,440
They're all people featured
 in magazines every month!

154
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:14,570
You, girl who is innocent like a white clover!

155
00:09:15,450 --> 00:09:18,070
That's Donato Gotoda of the auberge Tesoro!

156
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:21,950
You may be the reason for my existence.

157
00:09:21,950 --> 00:09:25,580
Why don't we talk through the night till dawn at my auberge?

158
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:26,830
Um, what?

159
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:27,830
Um, excuse me!

160
00:09:27,830 --> 00:09:31,050
Let go of her hand, Chef Gotoda.

161
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:32,420
Hinako.

162
00:09:32,420 --> 00:09:35,510
It's Inui Hinako of the Japanese restaurant Kirinoya!

163
00:09:36,590 --> 00:09:39,300
I'm sorry that you had such a frightening experience.

164
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:42,810
You're very cute, by the way.

165
00:09:43,810 --> 00:09:46,060
I'm sure you'd be very good to eat.

166
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,310
Hinako.

167
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:50,480
Chapelle-sensei's glaring at us.

168
00:09:50,860 --> 00:09:51,730
Let's go.

169
00:09:51,730 --> 00:09:52,860
Oh.

170
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:56,070
Please come by my restaurant sometime!

171
00:09:56,860 --> 00:09:58,410
Pssssh...

172
00:09:58,410 --> 00:09:59,910
Oh! That's...

173
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:02,870
That's the man who graduated first in his class

174
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:05,250
after getting the highest score ever on the graduation exam!

175
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:11,380
He turned down over 800 offers from 
high-caliber restaurants around the world.

176
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:15,840
Instead, he took the position of Executive Chef and Company Director of Tohtsuki Resorts!

177
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,130
Doujima Gin!

178
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:20,850
This is incredible.

179
00:10:21,210 --> 00:10:24,060
All the star chefs leading Japan's culinary world

180
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:26,640
are lined up in front of me!

181
00:10:28,060 --> 00:10:30,900
Welcome to my Tohtsuki Resort.

182
00:10:31,770 --> 00:10:36,990
Each of the alumni who have gathered here today is a chef who owns his or her own restaurant.

183
00:10:37,570 --> 00:10:40,030
For the next six days of the training camp,

184
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:43,700
we will treat you as we would our own staff.

185
00:10:44,330 --> 00:10:45,830
Do you understand what that entails?

186
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:48,160
Those who cannot perform to our expectations...

187
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:50,290
will be fired!

188
00:10:50,290 --> 00:10:51,500
Or in your case, expelled.

189
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:56,380
As you have already seen, at their discretion,
 you may be dismissed at the drop of a hat.

190
00:10:57,050 --> 00:10:59,090
I wish you all the best of luck.

191
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:03,700
Now, proceed to your groups!

192
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:06,270
We're all split up, but I wish you all the best!

193
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,400
I'm with you <i>again</i>?!

194
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,520
What's it to you?!

195
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,730
Later!

196
00:11:10,730 --> 00:11:11,770
Yeah!

197
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:15,070
Oh, don't forget we're having
a card game in Marui's room later!

198
00:11:15,070 --> 00:11:18,900
You don't all have to come
 to my room even during camp!

199
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:27,950
Wanna drink?

200
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:29,290
Sure.

201
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:35,790
It seems you're all here.

202
00:11:36,610 --> 00:11:39,760
In my class, you'll be working in pairs.

203
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:43,430
You'll be in the same pairs as in your first practicum of the semester.

204
00:11:43,430 --> 00:11:46,260
Please go to your workstations.

205
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:49,520
Thank goodness! I'm with you again, Souma-kun!

206
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,810
Yup, let's give this a whirl.

207
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:53,690
Yukihira Souma, is it?

208
00:11:53,690 --> 00:11:55,020
Yeah, so?

209
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:04,030
You've been grinding your foot
into mine for the last ten seconds,

210
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:06,080
so I guess I can assume it's intentional?

211
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,160
Of course.

212
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:10,160
I was wondering when I'd get to mess with you during camp,

213
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:13,460
but I didn't think I'd be lucky enough
 to get close to you in our first task.

214
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:17,210
I'll crush you, just like I did your shoe.

215
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:17,920
<i>Huh?</i>

216
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:21,630
U-Um, we already know it's going
 to be an intense camp.

217
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:23,380
W-We shouldn't be fighting on top of that.

218
00:12:23,380 --> 00:12:25,680
I can finally put you in your place.

219
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,600
That makes me happy, Yukihira Souma!

220
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,990
I see.

221
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:30,810
Well, good for you.

222
00:12:30,810 --> 00:12:33,560
I get the picture already, so move your foot!

223
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:35,770
Okay, everyone!

224
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,640
I'll be sitting right here,

225
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:42,740
so feel free to ask me any
 questions you might have.

226
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,660
Excuse me, Chef Inui,

227
00:12:45,660 --> 00:12:48,530
but we weren't given any instructions.

228
00:12:48,530 --> 00:12:50,160
Oh, is that right?

229
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:51,290
Let me see.

230
00:12:51,290 --> 00:12:53,410
Hm, my task for you is this.

231
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:58,880
Use the ingredients there to make a dish
 that could serve as a main course in Japanese cuisine.

232
00:13:00,170 --> 00:13:01,260
Ingredients? But...

233
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:03,720
There's nothing there.

234
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:05,720
Of course there is!

235
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,010
We're amid glorious nature, 
right next to a clear stream.

236
00:13:08,010 --> 00:13:09,970
There are ingredients galore.

237
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,850
We also have spices, condiments, and oil,

238
00:13:13,850 --> 00:13:15,390
not to mention cooking utensils.

239
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:19,570
You are welcome to use other tools, 
such as fishing poles.

240
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:24,490
We're on private property that is encircled by a fence.

241
00:13:24,490 --> 00:13:27,740
If you cross that fence, you will be disqualified.

242
00:13:28,420 --> 00:13:32,240
Obtain your ingredients from this limited space and prepare them.

243
00:13:32,710 --> 00:13:36,080
You will pass if you create a dish
 that I find satisfactory.

244
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:38,710
This session is two hours long,

245
00:13:38,710 --> 00:13:40,960
so you should probably get to it.

246
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:44,840
Huh? You mean we should've already started?!

247
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,340
Why didn't you say so?!

248
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:49,010
We have to figure out what we can fish up first!

249
00:13:49,010 --> 00:13:49,930
Sweetfish!

250
00:13:49,930 --> 00:13:51,720
We can just grill it with salt!

251
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,640
But are they even in season right now?!

252
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,350
Whatever! We have less than two hours!

253
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,850
Hurry!

254
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:00,400
It's face-off time, Yukihira!

255
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,320
What do you mean?

256
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:05,190
Let's decide who's the better chef.

257
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:09,160
Chef Inui, I'd like you to make the call.

258
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:13,580
Please use your rigorous judgment and decide whose cooking tastes better!

259
00:14:13,580 --> 00:14:15,750
Um, what?

260
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:18,330
That has nothing to do with my task, 
so I would prefer not to.

261
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,090
Oh. I suppose you're right.

262
00:14:23,090 --> 00:14:25,420
Hey, what're you gonna do?

263
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:28,870
Because you got on your high horse, 
you're making everyone uncomfortable.

264
